        <h1>LeetCode 3314: Construct the Minimum Bitwise Array I (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an array nums consisting of n prime integers. You need to construct an array ans of length n, such that, for each index i, the bitwise OR of ans[i] and ans[i] + 1 is equal to nums[i], i.e. ans[i] OR (ans[i] + 1) == nums[i]. Additionally, you must minimize each value of ans[i] in the resulting array. If it is not possible to find such a value for ans[i] that satisfies the condition, then set ans[i] = -1.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [2,3,5,7]<br/>
                Output: [-1,1,4,3]<br/>
                Explanation: For i = 0, there is no value for ans[0] that satisfies ans[0] OR (ans[0] + 1) = 2. So ans[0] = -1. For i = 1, the smallest ans[1] that satisfies ans[1] OR (ans[1] + 1) = 3 is 1. For i = 2, the smallest ans[2] that satisfies ans[2] OR (ans[2] + 1) = 5 is 4. For i = 3, the smallest ans[3] that satisfies ans[3] OR (ans[3] + 1) = 7 is 3.<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [11,13,31]<br/>
                Output: [9,12,15]<br/>
                Explanation: For i = 0, the smallest ans[0] that satisfies ans[0] OR (ans[0] + 1) = 11 is 9. For i = 1, the smallest ans[1] that satisfies ans[1] OR (ans[1] + 1) = 13 is 12. For i = 2, the smallest ans[2] that satisfies ans[2] OR (ans[2] + 1) = 31 is 15.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    vector&lt;int&gt; minBitwiseArray(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        vector&lt;int&gt; ans;
        
        for (int num : nums) {
            int result = -1;
            
            // Try all possible values from 0 to num-1
            for (int i = 0; i &lt; num; i++) {
                if ((i | (i + 1)) == num) {
                    result = i;
                    break;
                }
            }
            
            ans.push_back(result);
        }
        
        return ans;
    }
};</code></pre>
